Program: Outlook
Title: 17/09/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00xws00
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 18 Sep 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, David Simpson the British man who spent more than five months in prison in the Central African Republic after stumbling across the aftermath of a massacre. Also, the man tackling Delhi's monkey problem - Shyam has been working with langurs for 15 years and rides around with them perched on his scooter. He uses these larger monkeys to chase off smaller monkeys causing a nuisance in different areas of the city. Outlook's Suhail Haleem meets him at work. Show less